  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I stop Outlook from synchronising folders automatically?",
  "response": "To stop Outlook from automatically synchronizing folders, you can try these methods:\n\n1. For Microsoft 365/Outlook Desktop:\n- Go to File > Options > Advanced\n- Under \"Sync options\", uncheck \"Sync shared folders when switching between them\"\n\n2. For Outlook Web App:\n- Click the gear icon > View all Outlook settings\n- Go to Mail > Sync\n- Disable automatic sync settings\n\n3. For Exchange accounts:\n- Go to File > Account Settings\n- Select the account\n- Click \"Change\" or \"Modify\"\n- Uncheck \"Download shared folders automatically\"\n\n4. Registry edit (advanced users):\n- Open Registry Editor (regedit)\n- Navigate to HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Microsoft\\Office\\16.0\\Outlook\\Preferences\n- Create/modify DWORD value \"SyncSharedFolders\" and set to 0\n\n5. For cached mode:\n- File > Account Settings\n- Go to \"Data Files\" tab\n- Select account > Change\n- Adjust \"Download shared folders\" settings\n\nThe exact steps might vary slightly depending on your Outlook version. Always backup your data before making changes.",
